HEADWORD: Serai
<hw>Se*ra"i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>ser⟦amac⟧⟦ium⟧</ets>, or <ets>sar⟦amac⟧⟦ium⟧</ets>, a palace, a
king's court, a seraglio, an inn. Cf. <er>Caravansary</er>.]</ety>
<def>A palace; a seraglio; also, in the East, a place for the
accommodation of travelers; a caravansary, or rest house.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

